article.headline: Saint Louis 86, St. Bonaventure 62
article.story: ST. LOUIS -- Kwamain Mitchell scored 22 points Wednesday night, leading five Saint Louis players in double figures, and the Billikens reached their highest point total of the season in an 86-62 win over St. Bonaventure. Brian Conklin had 19 points, Mike McCall Jr. scored 15 points, Jordair Jett scored 13 and Dwayne Evans had 10 points and 11 rebounds for Saint Louis (17-5, 5-3 Atlantic 10). Demitrius Conger scored 13 points to lead the Bonnies (12-8, 5-3). He had 11 in the first half when St. Bonaventure led 36-34. The Bonnies shot 51 percent in the game, but the Billikens, who shot 52 percent, had eight more field goals in the second half. Da'Quan Cook had 12 points and Charlon Kloof scored 11 for the Bonnies.
